        "title": "[codex] feat(mcp): stage binary tool content for relay",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nPart of #87023.\n\nThis adds a conservative relay foundation for MCP binary content:\n\n- stage MCP `image`, `audio`, and blob-backed `resource` content into OpenClaw-owned outbound media attachments\n- expose those staged files through `details.media.attachments` so the existing channel relay extractor can hand them off\n- add a process-local host-owned MCP media registry so only files staged by OpenClaw can bypass the external-tool local-path filter\n\nThe model-facing transcript behavior stays compatible: valid MCP images still remain image blocks, while audio/resource blocks continue to degrade to text summaries for providers that do not accept those block types.\n\n## Safety\n\n- MCP-provenance arbitrary local paths remain blocked by the existing external-tool filter.\n- MCP servers cannot bless their own local paths; only host-staged media paths are registered.\n- Staging uses the existing outbound media store and media-core MIME/size caps, plus per-tool-result attachment-count and aggregate decoded-byte budgets with sequential staging.\n- Staging failures degrade to the existing tool-result content instead of failing the MCP tool call.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-tools.materialize.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.tools.media.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:src`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm openclaw --version`\n\n`$autoreview` was requested by the contributor guide, but no autoreview tool is available in this Codex session.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: After the unpadded-base64 follow-up, MCP `ImageContent`, `AudioContent`, and blob-backed binary `Content` from a real MCP stdio server are preserved as OpenClaw-owned outbound media attachments in MCP content order, then relayed through the existing tool-result media extractor/filter. The same run verifies that unstaged MCP local paths are still rejected.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw checkout at commit `303b6bc` on macOS, Node `25.9.0`, isolated `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-real-mcp-relay-unpadded.vXTPGT/openclaw.json`. `pnpm openclaw --version` started the real CLI and reported `OpenClaw 2026.6.8 (303b6bc)`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: Ran `pnpm openclaw --version`, then ran a live `node --import tsx` smoke that started a local stdio MCP server with `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`, connected via OpenClaw `createSessionMcpRuntime`, materialized the MCP tool through `materializeBundleMcpToolsForRun`, executed it with unpadded base64 payloads `TQ`, `TWE`, and `SGVsbG8`, and passed the result through `extractToolResultMediaArtifact` plus `filterToolResultMediaUrls`.\n- **Evidence after fix**: Terminal output from the live OpenClaw smoke at the latest pushed head:\n\n```text\nOPENCLAW_REAL_MCP_RELAY_PROOF_START\nopenclaw_config_path=/tmp/openclaw-real-mcp-relay-unpadded.vXTPGT/openclaw.json\nopenclaw_state_dir=/tmp/openclaw-real-mcp-relay-unpadded.vXTPGT\nmedia_dir=/tmp/openclaw-real-mcp-relay-unpadded.vXTPGT/media\ncatalog_servers=binaryProof\ncatalog_tools=binaryProof/relay_binary\nmaterialized_tool=binaryProof__relay_binary\nmodel_content_types=text,image,text,text\ndetails_media_source=mcp\ndetails_media_host_owned=true\nattachment_count=3\nattachment=image:image/png:binaryProof-relay_binary-1---8d9887df-929d-4e5d-9e16-260f3074ac11.png\nattachment=audio:audio/mpeg:binaryProof-relay_binary-2---cb761f22-5159-4938-9960-4961bea92fb9.mp3\nattachment=resource:application/pdf:binaryProof-relay_binary-3---5c8a2574-5f8e-4b9f-a384-cbbc251f0689.pdf\nextractor_media_count=3\nrelay_filtered_count=3\nstaged_file=binaryProof-relay_binary-1---8d9887df-929d-4e5d-9e16-260f3074ac11.png:exists=true:bytes=1\nstaged_file=binaryProof-relay_binary-2---cb761f22-5159-4938-9960-4961bea92fb9.mp3:exists=true:bytes=2\nstaged_file=binaryProof-relay_binary-3---5c8a2574-5f8e-4b9f-a384-cbbc251f0689.pdf:exists=true:bytes=5\nstaged_file_payloads=M|Ma|Hello\nspoofed_local_mcp_path_allowed=0\nOPENCLAW_REAL_MCP_RELAY_PROOF_END\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: OpenClaw connected to the real MCP stdio server, listed `binaryProof/relay_binary`, executed it, accepted SDK-compatible unpadded base64 for image/audio/resource blocks, staged one `image/png`, one `audio/mpeg`, and one `application/pdf` resource into the isolated OpenClaw media store, exposed all three through `details.media` with `source=mcp` and `hostOwned=true`, preserved content order, and the relay filter allowed exactly those three host-staged attachments while rejecting a spoofed MCP local path.\n- **Regression proof**: Focused unit coverage verifies unpadded MCP image/audio/resource base64 staging, invalid-character rejection, the 8-attachment cap, and aggregate decoded-byte capping before additional base64 blocks are decoded.\n- **CI follow-up proof**: Locally reran `pnpm lint --threads=8`, `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-tools.materialize.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.tools.media.test.ts --reporter=verbose`, `pnpm tsgo:test:src`, `git diff --check`, and `pnpm openclaw --version` after commit `303b6bc`.\n- **What was not tested**: Native Telegram/iMessage/Signal delivery was not exercised in this local proof; this PR intentionally stops at the shared OpenClaw MCP-to-tool-result media relay seam and leaves channel-specific UX/product behavior for follow-up review.\n",
